  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And let's go-- let's go to Canada.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, yes, my-- my mother-- since being a, uh, peasant girl, the, uh, her father sold-- had about four-- four hectares of land.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But [INAUDIBLE] four hectares of land, but it was-- and when they parents, my great-grandparents died, and I remained there with the two sisters and one brother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they divided up-- my mother had in there about 1 and 1/2 hectares.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was really good money-- good money at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But with a family of six, you had to have money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, uh, uh, uh, um, mother had some-- some relatives with a little bit of money, and she borrowed it from them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it took about four years before we could-- with dollar and dollar could send it back, because we arrived in-- in the spring in May-- May 1st, we landed in Edmonton, and we were up to next [INAUDIBLE] had in a Great Depression.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with a family like that, and she talked to a-- to a CPR, get quarter section, which was 106 [INAUDIBLE] and all forest.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had to clear the land, even for the-- for the one-room-- one-room house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, no, on-- on-- on the contrary.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It took also, it was a-- it was a-- a-- calvary for-- for my father to-- to acquire.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They wanted to get through to him, but when he applied for a-- for a-- for an exit visa from-- from the village, then-- then they held it back, you see.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was just a revenge, you know, to teach-- just to torture him, you see, because it was so-- so-- much-- so much hatred against.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First, he was-- he was-- a-- a-- he was classified as a Slovak.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
